cs.GT, cs.CE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MA

The paper proposes a market design for charger sharing, which involves game theory, mechanism design, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also considers the allocation and scheduling process, which falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The use of optimization techniques and the computation study suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper deals with the management of a two-sided market, which could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
